HEADWORD: Sea room
<hw>Sea" room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Room or space
at sea for a vessel to maneuver, drive, or scud, without peril of
running ashore or aground.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

